      Meme activism
   =20
 =20
I have  said in the  past that a good way to do shareholder activism these =
days is by appealing to retail investors with memes. You buy some stock in =
a company, you put out an open letter to the board saying =E2=80=9Cyou need=
 to start accepting Dogecoin, selling non-fungible tokens and installing Te=
sla chargers at your stores,=E2=80=9D everyone on Reddit is like =E2=80=9Ct=
his is cool, to the moon,=E2=80=9D the stock goes up, and you sell at a pro=
fit regardless of whether the company does anything or any of this makes se=
nse.I have  also said that the original meme-stock activist, Ryan Cohen, wh=
ose involvement in GameStop Corp. helped=C2=A0cause its stock to moon early=
 last year, did=C2=A0not=C2=A0particularly do this. He built a big stake in=
 GameStop, advocated pretty normal business-y things, became chairman of th=
e board and got actively involved in a digital transformation, and continue=
d to hold his stock even after its enormous run-up.Still he is very popular=
 on Reddit. If I were him I would definitely try to leverage that for some =
free money. Buy a big stake in a meme-y stock, announce the stake, say =E2=
=80=9CI=E2=80=99ve got plans to turn this into the next GameStop,=E2=80=9D =
it goes to the moon, maybe you sell before it actually becomes the next Gam=
eStop? I don=E2=80=99t know. It=E2=80=99s possible this will not work as we=
ll in the relatively serious world of 2022 as it did in the very meme-y 202=
1, but it  does seem to work:Bed Bath & Beyond Inc. shares had their bigges=
t gain in 30 years of trading after Ryan Cohen=E2=80=99s investment firm RC=
 Ventures disclosed a large stake in the retailer and asked that it conside=
r a sale of the whole company.The Union, New Jersey-based home-goods retail=
er jumped as much as 86% on Monday after Cohen said Bed Bath & Beyond shoul=
d consider selling itself to a well-capitalized buyer or sell its baby-prod=
ucts business. ...Cohen, co-founder of Chewy Inc. and chairman of GameStop =
Corp., has had a strong following of retail traders who piled into shares o=
f both the pet supplies provider and video-game retailer at the height of t=
he coronavirus pandemic with consumers stuck at home. GameStop surged 688% =
last year and 210% in 2020.Bed Bath & Beyond, a darling of so-called meme-s=
tock traders, reported quarterly sales that missed estimated and reduced it=
s outlook for sales and adjusted earnings per share for the current fiscal =
year when it released results in January.He should buy a big stake in AMC E=
ntertainment Holdings Inc. and send them a letter like =E2=80=9Cyou should =
be doing exactly what you are doing now but like 5% more of it.=E2=80=9D
