d that has a 10-year life and a 2% annual management fee and a 20% performa=
nce fee, in expectation you will pay about 20% of your investment to the ma=
nager in management fees. (Plus, you hope, and the manager hopes, even more=
 in performance fees.) I suppose they could =E2=80=A6=C2=A0just =E2=80=A6=
=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26940247.278=
